AU  - Tirole, Jean
T1  - Bubbly Liquidity
PY  - 2012
Y1  - 2012/04/01
DO  - 10.1093/restud/rdr039
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 79
IS  - 2
SP  - 678
EP  - 706
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - This paper analyses the possibility and the consequences of rational bubbles in a dynamic economy where financially constrained firms demand and supply liquidity. Bubbles are more likely to emerge, the scarcer the supply of outside liquidity and the more limited the pledgeability of corporate income; they crowd investment in (out) when liquidity is abundant (scarce). We analyse extensions with firm heterogeneity and stochastic bubbles.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/restud/rdr039
ER  - 



